{
  "texts": [
    "Our methodology leverages Graph Representation Learning applied to networks through Graph Neural Networks.",
    "Graph Representation Learning (GRL) is a method for encoding structural information of a graph into low-dimensional vectors.",
    "The mapping derived from projecting nodes or subgraphs of a graph into a vector space reflects the original graph's structure.",
    "GRL enables the use of learned embeddings as feature inputs for downstream machine learning tasks, leveraging graph structures for various applications such as node classification, link prediction, and graph visualization.",
    "Many GRL approaches have been developed over time, but we have chosen Graph Neural Networks that deal with node labels based on inductive strategies."
  ]
}